%p
  &bull; <strong>Dr. Peter A. Lewin</strong> was inducted into The College of Physicians of Philadelphia for his contributions to societal health. The contributions of Drexel's School of Biomedical Engineering resulted in elevation to Fellow grade three Faculty members in total: Dr. Banu Onaral, Dr. Paul Brandt-Rauf and Dr. Peter A. Lewin. Additionally, Biomed's graduate Dr. Michael Dellavecchia, who holds MD degree in ophthalmology, is among the College's Fellows.

